    <ns3:Summary>Delays between Bletchley and Bedford expected until 15:00</ns3:Summary>
    <ns3:Description>
        &lt;p&gt;Trains between Bletchley and Bedford may be delayed by up to 10 minutes due to urgent repairs to the
        track between these stations. This is expected until 15:00.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Check before you travel:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
        You can check your journey using the National Rail Enquiries real-time &lt;a
        href="http://ojp.nationalrail.co.uk/service/planjourney/search"&gt;Journey Planner&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Twitter:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
        If you would like to follow this incident on Twitter, please use &lt;a
        href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/Bletchley?f=tweets"&gt;#Bletchley&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
        You may be entitled to &lt;a href="http://www.nationalrail.co.uk/compensation"&gt;compensation&lt;/a&gt; if you
        experience a delay in completing your journey today. Please keep your train ticket and make a note of your
        journey, as both will be required to support any claim.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Feedback:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt; We want to make information better - tell us how! Fill out this online &lt;a
        href="http://www.nationalrail.co.uk/disruption_survey"&gt;Disruption Survey&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
    </ns3:Description>
